HEADWORD: Travers
<hw>Trav"ers</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>travers</ets>, breadth, extent from side, <ets>⟦agrave⟧
travers</ets>, <ets>en travers</ets>, <ets>de travers</ets>, across,
athwart. See <er>Traverse</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <def>Across;
athwart.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The earl . . . caused . . . high trees to be hewn down, and laid
<qex>travers</qex> one over another.</q> <rj><qau>Ld.
Berners.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

